
Book.create(:title => 'Chicago', :description => "This guide focuses on the interaction between Controller and View in the Model-View-Controller triangle. As you know, the Controller is responsible for orchestrating the whole process of handling a request in Rails, though it normally hands off any heavy code to the Model. But then, when it's time to send a response back to the user, the Controller hands things off to the View. It's that handoff that is the subject of this guide.", :price => 130, :author => 'Eddy Chou', :status => 'Single', :image_url => '1.jpg')
